# TypeScript & React standards

- Use TypeScript strict mode. Don't weaken it to make an error go away.
- Never use `any` unless explicitly justified with a comment; prefer `unknown` + narrowing.
- Prefer small, composable, pure functions over large stateful ones.
- Reuse existing project types and utilities before adding new ones.
- Keep components focused; lift shared logic into hooks or helpers rather than duplicating.
- Handle the error and loading states, not just the happy path.
